          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`PrimitiveOccurrencePosition` cannot represent type-alias targets even though the spec includes `type_alias.target`/TypeRef positions as scan targets. Since `CatalogueLinterRuleKind::ForbidPrimitiveInTypes.positions` is typed as `NonEmptyVec<PrimitiveOccurrencePosition>`, a catalogue entry such as a `type_alias` whose target is `String` cannot be configured or reported by the new rule, leaving an in-scope TypeRef position outside the contract. Add a type-alias-target position to this enum and have the evaluator classify that slot explicitly.",
