        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "T001 defines PrimitiveOccurrenceReport as only ordinary()/result_err() sets, and T005 later treats any ordinary hit as belonging to the caller-known outer catalogue position. That collapses the ordinary position vocabulary, so T004 cannot actually satisfy IN-02/AC-02 for param/return/bound occurrences nested inside function-type signatures, or for other non-field TypeRef positions, despite task-coverage.json mapping IN-02 and AC-02 to these tasks. The plan needs a report shape or evaluation flow that preserves the occurrence position instead of only ordinary vs result_err.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/catalogue-primitive-obsession-guard-2026-07-01/impl-plan.json",
              "line": 6,
              "category": "task-coverage gap"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:8b062466221d26649018ccf19ad55a3893bd39c7cafead67f623a9d8e945d044",
          "at": "2026-07-01T12:26:37Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`task-coverage.json` does not map T002, T003, or T006 to any spec element. Those tasks are present in `impl-plan.json`/`plan.md` (S2 and the first task in S4), but the coverage matrix only traces T001, T004, T005, T007, and T008, leaving three executable tasks without spec traceability.",
